    {
      "id": "intro",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Numbers 1 to 10",
      "body": "# Numbers in French\n\nThe first ten numbers are an everyday building block — you'll need them for time, prices, addresses, phone numbers, and counting almost anything.\n\n| FR | EN |\n|----|----|\n| un | one |\n| deux | two |\n| trois | three |\n| quatre | four |\n| cinq | five |\n| six | six |\n| sept | seven |\n| huit | eight |\n| neuf | nine |\n| dix | ten |\n\nNote the silent letters: **deux**, **trois**, **six**, **dix** all have a silent final consonant in most contexts."
    },
    {
